<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,399,391,417]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Macrobiotus pallarii</emphasis>
Maucci 
<number box="[507,565,391,417]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" value="1954.0">1954</number>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1436,391,698]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
I have collected 
<specimenCount box="[396,571,432,458]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" type="generic">
<number box="[396,440,432,458]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" value="191.0">191</number>
specimens
</specimenCount>
and 
<specimenCount box="[631,723,432,458]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" type="egg">
<number box="[631,660,432,458]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" value="30.0">30</number>
eggs
</specimenCount>
from all habitats but MT. Cuticle showed very small pores, sometimes difficult to observe. Animal and egg morphologies corresponded to descriptions in 
<bibRefCitation author="Ramazzotti" pageId="22" pageNumber="29" refString="Ramazzotti, G. &amp; Maucci, W. (1983) Il phylum Tardigrada. III edizione riveduta e aggiornata. Memorie dell'Istituto Italiano di Idrobiologia Dott. Marco de Marchi, 41, 1 - 1012." type="journal article" year="1983">
Ramazzotti &amp; Maucci (
<number box="[256,320,512,538]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" value="1983.0">1983</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. Lunules on the fourth pair of legs had teeth in one-third of the populations. I found between 
<number box="[151,180,552,578]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" value="14.0">14</number>
and 
<number box="[242,271,552,578]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" value="26.0">26</number>
processes per egg and between 
<number box="[662,677,552,578]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" value="6.0">6</number>
and 
<number box="[739,768,552,578]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" value="12.0">12</number>
polygonal areas at the base of each process. Body size ranged from 
<number box="[302,442,592,618]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" value="836.0" valueMax="1342.0" valueMin="330.0">330 to 1342</number>
μm, mean 
<number box="[572,616,592,618]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" value="723.0">723</number>
μm (SD 
<number box="[723,771,592,618]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" value="193.0">193</number>
). The species has been cited for Europe, Asia and 
<collectingCountry name="United States of America" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">America</collectingCountry>
. In the Iberian Peninsula, it has been recorded for 
<collectingCountry box="[793,860,632,658]" name="Spain" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Spain</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Lewin" box="[877,1114,632,658]" pageId="22" pageNumber="29" refString="Lewin Osorio, M. (1984) Nota sobre los tardigrados muscicolas de Cataluna. Publicaciones del Departamento de Zoologia (Barcelona), 10, 39 - 49." type="journal article" year="1984">
Lewin Osorio 
<number box="[1051,1114,632,658]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" value="1984.0">1984</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName box="[1136,1381,632,657]" class="Eutardigrada" family="Macrobiotidae" genus="Macrobiotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Parachela" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Tardigrada" rank="species" species="pallarii">
<emphasis box="[1136,1381,632,657]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Macrobiotus pallarii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was found at 
<number box="[255,284,672,698]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" value="30.0">30</number>
sampling points (Table 
<number box="[567,583,672,698]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" value="3.0">3</number>
).
</paragraph>
